(15, 1, '2023-06-12 03:53:54', '2023-06-12 03:53:54', '<b><a title=\"\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_of_Wallis_and_Futuna\">Sixty-two species of birds have been recorded in Wallis and Futuna</a></b>, a French <a title=\"Overseas collectivity\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overseas_collectivity\">overseas collectivity</a> in <a title=\"Polynesia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polynesia\">Polynesia</a> in the Pacific Ocean. It consists of three main islands, <a title=\"Wallis (island)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wallis_(island)\">Wallis</a> (Uvea), <a title=\"Futuna (Wallis and Futuna)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Futuna_(Wallis_and_Futuna)\">Futuna</a>, and <a title=\"Alofi Island\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alofi_Island\">Alofi Island</a>, along with several islets. Of the sixty-two bird species of the territory, five were <a title=\"Introduced species\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Introduced_species\">introduced</a> by humans. No species are <a title=\"Endemism\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endemism\">endemic</a> to the islands, but there are endemic <a title=\"Subspecies\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subspecies\">subspecies</a> of the <a title=\"Collared kingfisher\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collared_kingfisher\">collared kingfisher</a>, the <a title=\"Polynesian triller\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polynesian_triller\">Polynesian triller</a> <i>(example pictured)</i>, the <a title=\"Fiji shrikebill\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiji_shrikebill\">Fiji shrikebill</a>, and the <a title=\"Polynesian starling\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polynesian_starling\">Polynesian starling</a>. The <a title=\"Tongan ground dove\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tongan_ground_dove\">shy ground dove</a> has been <a title=\"Local extinction\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_extinction\">extirpated</a> from the islands, while the <a title=\"Blue-crowned lorikeet\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue-crowned_lorikeet\">blue-crowned lorikeet</a> is locally extinct on Uvea. <i>Ducula david</i>, an extinct species of <a title=\"Imperial pigeon\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imperial_pigeon\">imperial pigeon</a>, was <a title=\"Species description\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Species_description\">described</a> from <a title=\"Fossil\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fossil#Subfossil\">subfossil</a> remains on the islands and is thought to have been widespread before the arrival of humans. (<b><a title=\"List of birds of Wallis and Futuna\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_of_Wallis_and_Futuna\">Full list...</a></b>)', 'Hello bca 3', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-bca-3', '', '', '2023-06-12 03:53:54', '2023-06-12 03:53:54', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=15', 0, 'post', '', 0),
